description:
She attended the International School of Comics in Rome and worked as a designer for a few years on the series "The Great Classics" by Geronimo Stilton and made her debut in France with her first comic book, published by Clair de Lune, La Driade (tome 1 - Ashlyn). She collaborated with Mono magazine, with a panel painted by the number of 8-Mono. She drew a few pages in True Blood #6 for IDW. She has also drawn a few covers for various Zenescope series and at Aspen. She collaborated with the magazine and the book Noir Batman Crime Solver.

She currently works with the Top Cow on the series Rise of the Magi.
name: Tina Valentino
